<br>
Unfortunately, this is not the first time that Verant has made such poor design.  There are earlier ones (listed below).  The newbie-zone/Hole is just the worst example in the entire batch.<br>
<br>
1.  Kelethin -- how many newbies have died from falling off the treehouse ... subsequently losing their guild note or guild tunic (not a big deal)<br>
<br>
2.  Boats -- how many Freeport, Qeynos, or Erudite newbies have taken the boat, fallen out (via a bug), and drowned<br>
<br>
3.  Befallen -- how many &quot;explorers&quot; have fallen down the well or the trapfloor on the 2nd floor?  Two years ago, the Befallen Well used to be clogged with fully-dressed corpses.<br>
<br>
4.  Qeynos -- how many rogues have fallen into that hole near their guildhall?<br>
<br>
